subject: Beach Volleyball
lead_paragraph: Misty May-Treanor and Kerri Walsh, Olympic beach volleyball champions, lost for the first time in more than a year, dropping a 21-19, 10-21, 25-23 decision to Elaine Youngs and Nicole Branagh on Sunday in Mason, Ohio. The winning streak of May-Treanor and Walsh, the two-time Olympic gold medalists, ended at 112 matches and 19 titles. They last lost on Aug. 19, 2007, also to Branagh and Youngs.
